  "text": "Binds mRNA Processing Factors. To explore unique biological roles of WNK3, yeast two-hybrid screens were performed with three WNK3 baits and a neonatal mouse brain cDNA library. More than 100 putative WNK3 partners were identified; several are involved in mRNA splicing and translation (Fig. 1A) , suggesting a function of WNK3 in these processes. Several of these interactions were confirmed by coimmunoprecipitation (Fig. 1 B-G) . Consistent with yeast two-hybrid results, the WNK3 C terminus bound three splicing factors, Fox-1, Fox-2, and Celf4 ( Fig.  1 B-D) . WNK3 also bound the general translation elongation factor, EEF1A1, located not only at the ribosome but also in RNA processing complexes [CITATION_1] , and another translation elongation factor, EEF2 (Fig. 1 E-G) .",
